ng method invocation on a non-public class method after using setAccessible, which is okay if the method is public. For the Aspects14MultiScopeAspect, I'll need a reflect-config that covers all declared methods. I want to ensure I design tests that encompass all scenarios for getDeclaredMethod and invoke methods. Using assertions, possibly with AssertJ, seems like a plan. I should pay close attention to potential ambiguities in overloads and ensure my test styles align. Plus, I need to think about adding entries to the reflect-config.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying method invocation needs**\\n\\nI'm thinking that for getDeclaredMethod in the native context, it might need a query. And when it comes to Method.invoke, having the right invocation metadata is essential. I have to remember that the older format for the native reflect config, which includes allDeclaredMethods, actually enables that invocation. It's interesting to untangle these dependencies and ensure everything aligns for proper functionality.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_MkPmVBOTkyG9l8cG0lcQp5BW|fc_05345f1e869c834d0169f16f68ff8c8195a70b5370f8cb4515", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git status --short && find tests/src/org.aspectj/aspectjrt/1.9.6/src/test/java -type f -maxdepth 10 | sort", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 457, "output": 686, "cacheRead": 14848, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 15991, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777430363908, "responseId": "resp_05345f1e869c834d0169f16f5c3e2c8195af9dc813e8b6479e"}}
